CHOLERA, DIARRHEA AND DYSENTERY UPDATE (32): AMERICAS (CHILE) NON-TOXIGENIC
***************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Sat 25 Aug 2018
Source: Economía y Negocios Online, Chile, El Mercurio report [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
http://www.economiaynegocios.cl/noticias/noticias.asp?id=499099


The Ministry of Health confirmed an outbreak of cholera in the [Santiago] Metropolitan Region [MR] on Thu 23 Aug 2018: in the last 2 months, 14 suspected cases of the disease have been reported, of which 8 have been confirmed by laboratory tests.

Of the confirmed cases, the first was detected on 2 Aug 2018, in Pedro Aguirre Cerda; then 3 were registered on 9 Aug 2018 in Maipú, Quinta Normal, and Conchalí. The 5th case was located in El Bosque on 10 Aug 2018, and 5 days later, 2 more patients were confirmed in the communes of Quinta Normal and Santiago. The last was confirmed last night, 24 Aug 2018.

At the moment, the patients are concentrated from the center towards the west of the capital, although there are suspected cases in Vitacura, Las Condes, and Independencia. Yesterday, 24 Aug 2018, a new case was added, not yet confirmed, in Santiago.

The Undersecretary of Public Health, Paula Daza, assured that the strain of cholera detected does not correspond to the most aggressive one and added that the possible sources of contamination are still being studied. One hypothesis is that the origin is irrigation water. Meanwhile, the Health Department of the MR, Rosa Oyarce, reported that the public and private healthcare network was alerted, reinforcing the taking of samples in suspected cases and environmental monitoring in the region.

[Byline: Max Chávez]

