******
[2]
Date:: Fri 24 Aug 2018
Source: La Tercera, Chile [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
https://www.latercera.com/nacional/noticia/autoridades-descartan-alerta-sanitaria-brote-colera-llaman-la-prevencion/293592/


After the Ministry of Health yesterday, 23 Aug 2018, reported 13 suspected cases of cholera, 7 of which confirmed by the ISP [Public Health Institute], the Undersecretary of Public Health, Paula Daza, ruled out that the event implies a health alert.

As detailed by the authority, a "rigorous analysis" of the detected cases is being carried out, since until now it has not been confirmed that these could be linked. "There is no relationship between them and in fact they are from different communities," he said. Considering that it would be rather isolated facts, Daza was emphatic in stating that "it is not a health warning", but that what is being done is to deliver the corresponding information about the pathology, in order to "prevent this from spreading to the whole Metropolitan Region or the rest of the country. "

Regarding the state of health of the 3 people who were hospitalized, Daza indicated that so far "none have presented complications" and that they are individuals who had previous pathologies. In the same context, and emphasizing that the detected cases correspond to non-toxigenic _Vibrio cholerae_, the undersecretary recalled that this infection is not transmitted from person to person, but through the consumption of contaminated food or liquids.

As Independence Day [18 Sep 2018] celebrations (Fiestas Patrias) approach, the authority announced that the investigations associated with the detection of the bacteria that cause this disease will be increased.

[Byline: Catalina Batarce]

